<TITLE> Govt to explain steps for 156 in India </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)---- A High Court bench ordered the government to explain what steps it took to repatriate 156 Bangladeshi prisoners from India since expiry of their prison term. The bench of Justice AHM Shamsuddin Chowdhury and Justice Md Delwar Hossain on Tuesday issued the order. Muhammad Imran, director general of South Asia for the foreign ministry was given ten days to explain what steps the government had taken. On Feb 28 this year, Mostaq Ahmed Chowdhury, a lawyer of the Supreme Court filed a writ petition in this regard. On May 01 the HC asked the government to explain why an order would not be issued to bring back 156 Bangladeshis from India. The petition mentioned that a report published in the Daily Prothom Alo about 156 prisoners detained at Bahrampur jail in West Bengal, India even after their term had ended. bdnews24.
